description: Earlier mus, moos, from an Eastern Algonquian language name for the animal, such as Massachusett moos, mws, Narragansett moos or Penobscot mos (cognate to Abenaki moz), from Proto-Algonquian *mo·swa (“it strips”), referring to how a moose strips tree bark when feeding: compare Massachusett moos-u (“he strips, cuts smooth”).

nouns.description: moose (plural moose or (dated, rare) mooses or (non-standard, jocular) meese)

entries.meaning: (US, Canada) The largest member of the deer family (Alces americanus, sometimes included in Alces alces), of which the male has very large, palmate antlers.
examples: We saw a moose at the edge of the woods.

entries.meaning: (US, military, slang) An Asian girl taken as a lover.
examples: In military bases in the rear areas it was common for soldiers to have a moose.
